description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An excellent opportunity has arisen for a Point of Care Testing (POCT) Co-ordinator to maintain the Point of Care Testing (POCT) Service at Whittington Hospital. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role includes management of a wide range of POCT analysers and devices and the maintenance, training, competency, quality assurance and governance of these pieces of equipment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a motivated, enthusiastic and articulate HCPC registered biomedical scientist for this role. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post-holder will work relatively independently, supported by the Quality Manager and the Clinical Biochemist to deliver the POCT service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Given the outward facing nature of this role, the successful individual will need to have good organisational and communication skills. Experience with in PoCT and quality management would be desirable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTope Adebisi-DanielJob titleQuality ManagerEmail addresstope.adebisi-daniel@nhs.netTelephone number0207 288 3130&lt;/p&gt;
